Špilberk Castle.label: Špilberk Castle
Špilberk Castle.description: Špilberk Castle is an old castle on the hilltop in Brno, Southern Moravia. It began to be built as early as the first half of the 13th century by the Přemyslid kings and complete by King Ottokar II of Bohemia. Wikipedia

101 California Street.label: 101 California Street
101 California Street.description: 101 California Street is a 48-story office skyscraper completed in 1982 in the Financial District of San Francisco, California. Wikipedia

120 Collins Street.label: 120 Collins Street
120 Collins Street.description: 120 Collins Street is a 265-metre skyscraper in Melbourne, Victoria, Australia. Built from 1989 to 1991 and comprises 50 levels of office accommodation and 4 levels of plant. Wikipedia

191 Peachtree Tower.label: 191 Peachtree Tower
191 Peachtree Tower.description: One Ninety One Peachtree Tower is a 235 m 50-story skyscraper in Atlanta, Georgia. Designed by Johnson/Burgee Architects and Kendall/Heaton Associates Inc, the building was completed in 1990 and is the ... Wikipedia

300 North LaSalle.label: 300 North LaSalle
300 North LaSalle.description: 300 North LaSalle is a 60-story mixed-use building, constructed from 2006 to 2009, located on the north bank of the Chicago River on the Near North Side community area of Chicago, Illinois, United States. Wikipedia

33 South Sixth.label: 33 South Sixth
33 South Sixth.description: 33 South Sixth, formerly known as International Multifoods Tower, is a skyscraper in Minneapolis, Minnesota. It was designed by Skidmore, Owings and Merrill and stands 52 stories tall at 668 ft. Wikipedia

345 Park Avenue.label: 345 Park Avenue
345 Park Avenue.description: 345 Park Avenue is a 634-foot tall building in Manhattan, New York City that occupies a full city block with the front on Park Avenue, the back on Lexington Avenue, between 51st and 52nd Streets. Wikipedia

360 Condominiums.label: 360 Condominiums
360 Condominiums.description: The Austin 360 Condominiums Tower is a residential skyscraper at 360 Nueces Street, Downtown Austin, Texas, United States, standing 562' 9" tall with 44 floors and 430 rooms with over 14,000 sq ft of retail space. Wikipedia

555 17th Street.label: 555 17th Street
555 17th Street.description: 555 17th Street, formerly known as the Anaconda Tower and the Qwest Tower, is a skyscraper in Denver, Colorado. The building was completed in 1978, and rises 40 floors and 507 feet in height. Wikipedia

611 Place.label: 611 Place
611 Place.description: 611 Place is a 189 m skyscraper at 611 West 6th Street in downtown Los Angeles, California, designed by William L. Pereira & Associates and completed in 1969. Wikipedia

777 Tower.label: 777 Tower
777 Tower.description: 777 Tower is a 221 m, 52-story office building designed by César Pelli in downtown Los Angeles, California. Wikipedia

AEGON Center.label: AEGON Center
AEGON Center.description: The AEGON Center is a skyscraper in Downtown Louisville, Kentucky and located at 400 West Market Street. Wikipedia

Abraj Al Bait.label: Abraj Al Bait
Abraj Al Bait.description: The Abraj Al-Bait Towers, also known as the Mecca Royal Hotel Clock Tower, is a government-owned building complex in Mecca, Saudi Arabia. Wikipedia

Accademia.label: Accademia di Belle Arti Firenze
Accademia.description: The Accademia di Belle Arti di Firenze is an art academy in Florence, Italy. Wikipedia

Admiralty Head Light.label: Admiralty Head Light
Admiralty Head Light.description: The Admiralty Head Light is a lighthouse located in Fort Casey State Park near Coupeville on Whidbey Island, Washington. Wikipedia

Akron Art Museum.label: Akron Art Museum
Akron Art Museum.description:
The Akron Art Museum is an art museum in Akron, Ohio, USA.
The museum first opened its doors on February 1, 1922, as the Akron Art Institute. It was located in two borrowed rooms in the basement of the public library. Wikipedia

Albertina.label: Albertina
Albertina.description: The Albertina is a museum in the Innere Stadt of Vienna, Austria. It houses one of the largest and most important print rooms in the world with approximately 65,000 drawings and approximately 1 million ... Wikipedia

All Saints' Church, Wittenberg.label: All Saints' Church, Wittenberg
All Saints' Church, Wittenberg.description: All Saints' Church, commonly referred to as Schloßkirche to distinguish it from the Stadtkirche of St. Mary — and sometimes known as the Reformation Memorial Church — was a Catholic church which later ... Wikipedia

Almendres Cromlech.label: Almendres Cromlech
Almendres Cromlech.description: The Cromlech of the Almendres megalithic complex, located near Guadalupe, in the civil parish of Nossa Senhora de Guadalupe, municipality of Évora, is the largest existing group of structured menhirs ... Wikipedia

Andersonville National Historic Site.label: Andersonville National Historic Site
Andersonville National Historic Site.description: The Andersonville National Historic Site, located near Andersonville, Georgia, preserves the former Camp Sumter, a Confederate prisoner-of-war camp during the American Civil War. Wikipedia

Anta Grande do Zambujeiro.label: Anta Grande do Zambujeiro
Anta Grande do Zambujeiro.description: Anta Grande do Zambujeiro is a megalithic monument located in Nossa Senhora da Tourega, near Valverde, in the municipality of Évora, considered one of the biggest such structures in the Iberian Peninsula. Wikipedia

Archives of American Art.label: Archives of American Art
Archives of American Art.description: The Archives of American Art is the largest collection of primary resources documenting the history of the visual arts in the United States. Wikipedia

Arlene Schnitzer Concert Hall.label: Arlene Schnitzer Concert Hall, Portland
Arlene Schnitzer Concert Hall.description: The Arlene Schnitzer Concert Hall, opened as the Portland Publix Theater before becoming the Paramount after 1930, is a historic theater building and performing arts center in Portland, Oregon, United States. Wikipedia

Atlantis, The Palm.label: Atlantis, The Palm
Atlantis, The Palm.description: Atlantis, The Palm is a resort located on Dubai’s reclaimed artificial island The Palm. It was the first resort to be built on the island and is based on the myth of Atlantis includes distinct Arabian elements. Wikipedia
Address: Palm Jumeirah - Dubai - United Arab Emirates

Augsburg Town Hall.label: Augsburg Town Hall
Augsburg Town Hall.description: The Town Hall of Augsburg is the administrative centre of Augsburg, Bavaria, Germany, and one of the most significant secular buildings of the Renaissance style north of the Alps. Wikipedia

Aurora Place.label: Aurora Place
Aurora Place.description: Aurora Place is the common name of Renzo Piano's award-winning office tower and residential block on Macquarie Street in Sydney, Australia. Its official name is the RBS Tower building. Wikipedia

Austin Dam.label: Austin Dam
Austin Dam.description: Austin Dam was a dam in the Freeman Run Valley, Potter County, Pennsylvania, which serviced the Bayless Pulp & Paper Mill. A failure of the dam in 1911 caused significant destruction in the valley below. Wikipedia

Aviano Air Base.label: Aviano Air Base
Aviano Air Base.description: Aviano Air Base is a NATO base in northeastern Italy, in the Friuli-Venezia Giulia region. It is located in the Aviano municipality, at the foot of the Carnic Pre-Alps, or Southern Carnic Alps, about 15 kilometers from Pordenone. Wikipedia

BMW Headquarters.label: BMW Headquarters
BMW Headquarters.description: BMW Headquarters is a Munich landmark which has served as world headquarters for the Bavarian automaker BMW for over 40 years. It was declared a protected historic building in 1999. Extensive renovations commenced in 2004 and were completed in 2006. Wikipedia

BMW Museum.label: BMW Museum
BMW Museum.description:
The BMW Museum is an automobile museum in Munich, Germany. Located near the Olympiapark, it deals with the history of the automobile manufacturer BMW.
The museum was established in 1973, shortly after the Summer Olympics opened. Wikipedia

BOK Tower.label: Bok Tower Gardens
BOK Tower.description: Bok Tower Gardens is a botanical garden and bird sanctuary, located north of Lake Wales, Florida, United States. Wikipedia

Bank of America Tower (Jacksonville).label: Bank of America Tower
Bank of America Tower (Jacksonville).description: The Bank of America Tower is a 617 ft skyscraper in downtown Jacksonville, Florida, United States. It is the tallest building in Jacksonville, and the ninth-tallest in the state of Florida. Wikipedia

Bath Abbey.label: Bath Abbey
Bath Abbey.description: The Abbey Church of Saint Peter and Saint Paul, Bath, commonly known as Bath Abbey, is an Anglican parish church and a former Benedictine monastery in Bath, Somerset, England. Wikipedia

Beit Rubinstein.label: Beit Rubinstein
Beit Rubinstein.description: Rubinstein Building is a landmark skyscraper in Tel Aviv, Israel. The building was named after its developer, Rubinstein and Company. It was designed by Freiberger Architects. Wikipedia

Bellevue Palace (Germany).label: Bellevue Palace
Bellevue Palace (Germany).description: Bellevue Palace, located in Berlin's Tiergarten district, has been the official residence of the President of Germany since 1994. Wikipedia

Bentall 5.label: Bentall 5
Bentall 5.description: Bentall 5 or Five Bentall Centre is a 35-floor skyscraper located at 550 Burrard Street in Downtown Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada. Part of the Bentall Centre complex, it stands at 140 m, making it the 8th-tallest building in the city. Wikipedia

Berjaya Times Square.label: Berjaya Times Square
Berjaya Times Square.description: Berjaya Times Square Kuala Lumpur is a 48-storey, 203 m twin tower, hotel, condominium, indoor amusement park and shopping centre complex in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. Wikipedia

Bibliothèque Sainte-Barbe.label: Sainte-Barbe Library
Bibliothèque Sainte-Barbe.description: Sainte-Barbe Library is an inter-university library in Paris, France that opened in March 2009. It is located in the buildings of the former College of St. Barbara, and has been registered as a historical monument from 9 December 1999. Wikipedia

Österreichische Galerie Belvedere.label: Österreichische Galerie Belvedere
Österreichische Galerie Belvedere.description: The Österreichische Galerie Belvedere is a museum housed in the Belvedere palace, in Vienna, Austria. Wikipedia

Beylerbeyi Palace.label: Beylerbeyi Palace
Beylerbeyi Palace.description: The Beylerbeyi Palace is located in the Beylerbeyi neighbourhood of Istanbul, Turkey at the Asian side of the Bosphorus. An Imperial Ottoman summer residence built in the 1860s, it is now situated immediately north of the 1973 Bosphorus Bridge. Wikipedia

Borobudur.label: Borobudur
Borobudur.description: Borobudur, or Barabudur, is a 9th-century Mahayana Buddhist Temple in Magelang, Central Java, Indonesia. Wikipedia

Bosmal City Center.label: Bosmal City Center
Bosmal City Center.description: The Bosmal City Center is a business and residential tower located in Sarajevo, Bosnia and Herzegovina. Standing 118 m high, it is the second tallest residential building in the Balkans. Wikipedia

Bradford Cathedral.label: Bradford Cathedral
Bradford Cathedral.description: Bradford Cathedral, full name Cathedral Church of St Peter, is situated in the heart of Bradford in West Yorkshire, England, on a site used for Christian worship since the 8th century when missionaries based in Dewsbury evangelised the region. Wikipedia

Bressay Lighthouse.label: Bressay Lighthouse
Bressay Lighthouse.description: Bressay Lighthouse is a lighthouse in the Shetland Islands, Scotland, 4 kilometres south-east of Lerwick. It is located on the island of Bressay at Kirkabister Ness overlooking Bressay Sound. Wikipedia

Bridgeman Art Library.label: Bridgeman Art Library
Bridgeman Art Library.description: The Bridgeman Art Library, based in London, Paris, New York and Berlin, provides one of the largest archives for reproductions of works of art in the world. Wikipedia

Bull Ring, Birmingham.label: Bull Ring, Birmingham
Bull Ring, Birmingham.description: The Bull Ring is a major commercial area of Birmingham. It has been an important feature of Birmingham since the Middle Ages, when its market was first held. Wikipedia

Butser Ancient Farm.label: Butser Ancient Farm
Butser Ancient Farm.description: Butser Ancient Farm is an archaeological open air museum located near to Petersfield in Hampshire, southern England. Wikipedia

Cairo Tower.label: Cairo Tower
Cairo Tower.description: The Cairo Tower is a free-standing concrete tower located in Cairo, Egypt. At 187 m, it has been the tallest structure in Egypt and North Africa about 50 years. Wikipedia

Calke Abbey.label: Calke Abbey
Calke Abbey.description:
Calke Abbey is a Grade I listed country house near Ticknall, Derbyshire, England, in the care of the charitable National Trust.
The site was an Augustinian priory from the 12th century until its dissolution by Henry VIII. Wikipedia

Campbell Mithun Tower.label: Campbell Mithun Tower
Campbell Mithun Tower.description: The Campbell Mithun Tower in Minneapolis, Minnesota, USA is a 42-floor tower located on 9th Street and 3rd Avenue. Wikipedia

Cape Canaveral Air Force Station.label: Cape Canaveral Air Force Station
Cape Canaveral Air Force Station.description: Cape Canaveral Air Force Station is an installation of the United States Air Force Space Command's 45th Space Wing, headquartered at nearby Patrick Air Force Base. Wikipedia

Carew Tower.label: Carew Tower
Carew Tower.description: Carew Tower is a 49-story, 574-foot building completed in 1930 in the heart of downtown Cincinnati, Ohio, overlooking the Ohio River waterfront. Wikipedia

Casa Malaparte.label: Casa Malaparte
Casa Malaparte.description: Casa Malaparte is a house on Punta Massullo, on the eastern side of the Isle of Capri, Italy. It is one of the best examples of Italian modern and contemporary architecture. Wikipedia

Casapueblo.label: Casapueblo
Casapueblo.description: Casapueblo is the house of Uruguayan artist Carlos Páez Vilaró, located in Punta Ballena near Punta del Este, Uruguay. It is a homage to the artist's son Carlitos Paez, one of the sixteen survivors of the crash of Uruguayan Air Force Flight 571. Wikipedia

Castle Solitude.label: Castle Solitude
Castle Solitude.description: Castle Solitude in Stuttgart, Germany, was built as a hunting lodge between 1764 and 1769 under Duke Karl Eugen of Württemberg. It is not a true castle, but rather a rococo palace. Since 1956 the area is part of the urban district of Stuttgart-West. Wikipedia

Cathedral of La Laguna.label: La Laguna Cathedral
Cathedral of La Laguna.description: The Cathedral of San Cristóbal de La Laguna or Catedral de Nuestra Señora de los Remedios is a Catholic cathedral in Tenerife, Spain. Begun in 1904 and completed in 1915, it is dedicated to the Virgin of Los Remedios. Wikipedia

Cathedral of the Archangel.label: Cathedral of the Archangel
Cathedral of the Archangel.description: The Cathedral of the Archangel is a Russian Orthodox church dedicated to the Archangel Michael. It is located in Cathedral Square of the Moscow Kremlin in Russia between the Great Kremlin Palace and the Ivan the Great Bell Tower. Wikipedia

Château de Bagnolet, Paris.label: Château de Bagnolet, Paris
Château de Bagnolet, Paris.description: The Château de Bagnolet was a small château situated in the Paris suburb of Bagnolet, France, 5.2 km from the center of the city. Wikipedia

Chase Tower (Dallas).label: Chase Tower
Chase Tower (Dallas).description: Chase Tower is a 225 m, 55-story postmodern skyscraper at 2200 Ross Avenue in the City Center District of downtown Dallas, Texas. Wikipedia

Cheung Kong Center.label: Cheung Kong Center
Cheung Kong Center.description: Cheung Kong Center is a skyscraper in Central, Hong Kong designed by Cesar Pelli. It is 68 stories tall with height of 283 m and a gross floor area of 1,260,000-square-foot. When completed in 1999, it was the third-tallest building in the city. Wikipedia

Chicago Temple Building.label: Chicago Temple Building
Chicago Temple Building.description: The Chicago Temple Building is a 173 meter tall skyscraper church located at 77 W. Washington St. in Chicago, Illinois, United States. It is home to the congregation of the First United Methodist Church of Chicago. Wikipedia

Chichester Cathedral.label: Chichester Cathedral
Chichester Cathedral.description: The Cathedral Church of the Holy Trinity, otherwise called Chichester Cathedral, is the seat of the Anglican Bishop of Chichester. It is located in Chichester, in Sussex, England. Wikipedia

Chilehaus.label: Chilehaus
Chilehaus.description: The Chilehaus is a ten-story office building in Hamburg, Germany. It is located in the Kontorhausviertel. It is an exceptional example of the 1920s Brick Expressionism style of architecture. Wikipedia

Christ Church Cathedral, Dublin.label: Christ Church Cathedral, Dublin
Christ Church Cathedral, Dublin.description: Christ Church Cathedral is the cathedral of the United Dioceses of Dublin and Glendalough and the cathedral of the Ecclesiastical province of the United Provinces of Dublin and Cashel in the Church of Ireland. Wikipedia

Citigroup Center (Los Angeles).label: Citigroup Center
Citigroup Center (Los Angeles).description: Citigroup Center is a 625 ft 48-story skyscraper at 444 S. Flower Street in the Bunker Hill area of downtown Los Angeles, California. When completed in 1979, the tower was the fifth-tallest in the city—as of 2009, it is the eleventh. Wikipedia

City-Hochhaus Leipzig.label: City-Hochhaus Leipzig
City-Hochhaus Leipzig.description: City-Hochhaus is 36-storey skyscraper in Leipzig, Germany. At 142 m, it is the tallest multistory building in Leipzig. The tower was designed by architect Hermann Henselmann in the shape of an open book, and built between 1968 and 1972. Wikipedia

City Tower (Prague).label: City Tower
City Tower (Prague).description:
City Tower is a skyscraper in Prague, the second tallest one in the Czech Republic with 109 m in height.
Construction started in 1985 and the building was designated as a headquarters of Československý rozhlas. Wikipedia

Clinton–Kalamazoo Canal.label: Clinton–Kalamazoo Canal
Clinton–Kalamazoo Canal.description: The Clinton–Kalamazoo Canal is an abandoned canal in Michigan that was only partially completed. The canal was to connect Lake St. Clair with Lake Michigan. Wikipedia

Derby Central Library.label: Derby Central Library
Derby Central Library.description: Derby Central Library was established in 1879 with Derby Museum and Art Gallery, in a red brick building designed in the Domestic Flemish Gothic style by Richard Knill Freeman and given to Derby by Michael Thomas Bass. Wikipedia

Coit Tower.label: Coit Tower
Coit Tower.description: Coit Tower, also known as the Lillian Coit Memorial Tower, is a 210-foot tower in the Telegraph Hill neighborhood of San Francisco, California. Wikipedia

Deutsches Schauspielhaus.label: Deutsches Schauspielhaus
Deutsches Schauspielhaus.description: The Deutsches Schauspielhaus is a theatre in the St. Georg quarter of the city of Hamburg, Germany. With a capacity for 1192 spectators, it places it as Germany's largest theatre. Wikipedia

Dialogue in the Dark.label: Dialogue in the Dark
Dialogue in the Dark.description: Dialogue in the Dark is an awareness raising exhibition and franchise, as well as a social business. In Dialogue in the Dark, blind guides lead visitors in small groups through different settings in absolute darkness. Wikipedia

Donauturm.label: Donauturm
Donauturm.description: The Vienna Donauturm[p], opened in April 1964, is the tallest structure in Austria, at 252 metres, and among the 75 tallest towers in the world. The tower is located near the north bank of the Danube River in the district of Donaustadt. Wikipedia

Dore Abbey.label: Dore Abbey
Dore Abbey.description: Dore Abbey is a former Cistercian abbey in the village of Abbey Dore in the Golden Valley, Herefordshire, England. Wikipedia

Dormition Cathedral, Moscow.label: Dormition Cathedral, Moscow
Dormition Cathedral, Moscow.description: The Cathedral of the Dormition is a Russian Orthodox church dedicated to the Dormition of the Theotokos. Wikipedia

Duke Energy Center.label: Duke Energy Convention Center
Duke Energy Center.description: The Duke Energy Convention Center is a convention center located in downtown Cincinnati, Ohio, United States, covering two city blocks bounded by Elm Street, 5th Street, 6th Street, and Central Avenue. Wikipedia

Dunfermline Abbey.label: Dunfermline Abbey
Dunfermline Abbey.description: Dunfermline Abbey is a Church of Scotland Parish Church located in Dunfermline, Fife, Scotland. In 2002 the congregation had 806 members. The minister is the Reverend MaryAnn R. Rennie. Wikipedia

Dung Gate.label: Dung Gate
Dung Gate.description:
The Dung Gate is one of the gates in the walls of the Old City of Jerusalem.
The gate is situated near the southeast corner of the old city, southwest of the Temple Mount. Wikipedia

Dyess Air Force Base.label: Dyess Air Force Base
Dyess Air Force Base.description:
Dyess Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located approximately 7 miles southwest of Abilene, Texas.
The host unit at Dyess is the 7th Bomb Wing assigned to the Air Combat Command Twelfth Air Force. Wikipedia

Eddystone Lighthouse.label: Eddystone Lighthouse
Eddystone Lighthouse.description: The Eddystone Lighthouse is on the dangerous Eddystone Rocks, 9 statute miles south of Rame Head, United Kingdom. While Rame Head is in Cornwall, the rocks are in Devon and composed of Precambrian gneiss. Wikipedia

Edwards Air Force Base.label: Edwards Air Force Base
Edwards Air Force Base.description: Edwards Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located approximately 22 miles northeast of Lancaster, California. Wikipedia

Eisenberg Castle.label: Eisenberg Castle
Eisenberg Castle.description: Eisenberg Castle is a medieval hilltop castle ruin north of Pfronten, Bavaria, Germany built in the 14th century. Wikipedia

El Paso Energy Building.label: El Paso Energy Building
El Paso Energy Building.description: The El Paso Energy Building is a 502-foot tall skyscraper in Houston, Texas. It was completed in 1963 and has 33 floors. It was originally known as the Tenneco Building. It is the 28th tallest building in the city. Wikipedia

Electricity Museum (Lisbon).label: Electricity Museum
Electricity Museum (Lisbon).description: The Electricity Museum is a cultural centre that presents the evolution of Energy with a Museum of Science and Industrial Archaeology concept, where themed and experimental exhibits live side by side with a great variety of cultural events. Wikipedia

Ellsworth Air Force Base.label: Ellsworth Air Force Base
Ellsworth Air Force Base.description: Ellsworth Air Force Base is a United States Air Force base located approximately 10 miles northeast of Rapid City, South Dakota just north of Box Elder, South Dakota. Wikipedia

Elwha Dam.label: Elwha Dam
Elwha Dam.description: The Elwha Dam was a 108-ft high dam located in the United States, in the state of Washington, on the Elwha River approximately 4.9 miles upstream from the mouth of the river on the Strait of Juan de Fuca. Wikipedia

Embarcadero West.label: Embarcadero West
Embarcadero West.description: Embarcadero West is a 34-story, 123.1 m office skyscraper in the Financial District of San Francisco, California. The building is part of the Embarcadero Center, which is a complex of five office towers and two hotels. Wikipedia

Enterprise Plaza.label: Enterprise Plaza
Enterprise Plaza.description: Enterprise Plaza is a 55-story, 230 m skyscraper at 1100 Louisiana Street in downtown Houston, Texas The headquarters of Enterprise Products is located in the Enterprise Plaza. Enbridge's Houston offices are in Enterprise. Wikipedia

Equitable Building (Manhattan).label: Equitable Building
Equitable Building (Manhattan).description: The Equitable Building is a 38-story office building in New York City, located at 120 Broadway between Pine and Cedar Streets in the Financial District of Lower Manhattan. Wikipedia

Eureka Tower.label: Eureka Tower
Eureka Tower.description: Eureka Tower is a 297.3-metre skyscraper located in the Southbank precinct of Melbourne, Victoria, Australia. Construction began in August 2002 and the exterior completed on 1 June 2006. Wikipedia

Fifth Avenue Place (Pittsburgh).label: Fifth Avenue Place
Fifth Avenue Place (Pittsburgh).description:
Fifth Avenue Place is a skyscraper in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. United States.
The building was completed in 1988 and it has 31 floors. Located at the corner of Liberty Avenue and Fifth Avenue, it rises 616 feet above Downtown Pittsburgh. Wikipedia

Europa Tower.label: Europa Tower
Europa Tower.description: The Europa Tower is the tallest skyscraper in the Baltic states. It is located in a district of Lithuania's capital, Vilnius, called Šnipiškės. It rises 148 meters above ground level. Wikipedia

Figueroa at Wilshire.label: Figueroa at Wilshire
Figueroa at Wilshire.description: Figueroa at Wilshire, formerly Sanwa Bank Plaza, is a 53-storey, 219 m skyscraper in Los Angeles, California. It is the eighth tallest building in Los Angeles. Wikipedia

Exploratorium.label: Exploratorium
Exploratorium.description: The Exploratorium is a museum in San Francisco whose stated mission is to change the way the world learns. Wikipedia
